## 4️⃣ OCR & OpenCV (Computer Vision)

### Dual OCR Engine

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph "cv.so"
        A["OpenCV 3.4.20"] --> B["Image Processing"]
        C["Paddle-Lite 2.14-rc"] --> D["PaddleOCR<br/>(Neural Network)"]
        B --> D
    end
    
    subgraph "tess_ocr.so"
        E["Tesseract 3.02.02"] --> F["Traditional OCR"]
        G["Leptonica"] --> F
    end
    
    H["screen.ocr_text()"] --> A
    H --> E
```

### cv.so — OpenCV + PaddleOCR

| Component | Version | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| **OpenCV** | 3.4.20 | Image processing core |
| **Paddle-Lite** | 2.14-rc | Deep learning inference (mobile-optimized) |
| **PaddleOCR** | ppocr_ch model | Chinese + multilingual OCR via neural network |
| **libjpeg-turbo** | 2.1.2-62 | Fast JPEG decode/encode |
| **libpng** | 1.6.37 | PNG support |
| **libwebp** | bundled | WebP support |
| **quirc** | bundled | QR code detection |
| **protobuf** | bundled | ML model serialization |
| **MetalPerformanceShaders** | linked | GPU-accelerated inference |

**Model path**: `/var/mobile/Media/1ferver/models/ppocr_ch`

#### OpenCV Functions (exposed via JSC CanvasRenderingContext2D)

```javascript
// Polyfill gắn vào CanvasRenderingContext2D.prototype
ctx.resize(w, h)              // cv::resize
ctx.resize_copy(w, h)         // cv::resize (copy)
ctx.find_polygon(...)         // cv::findContours + approxPolyDP
ctx.compare_image(ref)        // cv::matchTemplate / compare
ctx.to_shapes(...)            // Contour → shape objects
ctx.find_shapes(...)          // Find specific shapes
ctx.detect_templates(tmpl)    // Template matching
```

**Build info**: Compiled by `/Users/havonz/Projects/opencv-3.4.20/` with OpenMP support.

### tess_ocr.so — Tesseract OCR

| Component | Version | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| **Tesseract** | 3.02.02 | Traditional OCR engine |
| **Leptonica** | bundled | Image preprocessing (binarization, deskew, etc.) |
| **Accelerate** | system | SIMD optimization |

**Tessdata path**: `/var/mobile/Media/1ferver/tessdata`
**Output format**: hOCR (HTML-based OCR format với bounding boxes)

#### OCR API Flow

```javascript
// High-level API trong screen module
screen.ocr_text(left, top, right, bottom, options, binopt)
// 1. Lấy kept canvas context
// 2. Crop region (normalizeRect)
// 3. Gọi ctx.ocr_text(options, binopt) — native binding
// 4. Adjust bounding box coordinates (+ rect.left/top offset)
// 5. Return [text, [{x, y, w, h, confidence, text}, ...]]
```

